                <p><a>Open this file in the Lurch web app</a></p>
                
            </div>
        
            <div id="metadata" style="display: none;"><div data-category="settings" data-key="shell style" data-value-type="json">"boxed"</div><div data-category="main" data-key="header" data-value-type="html"></div></div>
            <div id="document"><h1>Arithmetic in <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{N}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<p>The Arithmetic Rule for the natural numbers is a special built-in validation tool that Lurch provides for evaluating arithmetic identities and inequalities in the natural numbers.&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Arithmetic in the Natural Numbers Rule.&nbsp; </strong>We allow <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Arithmetic(NN)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Arithmetic</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.68889em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> to justify equations or inequality which only involves natural number constants (e.g. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;3, &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">3,</span></span></span></span></span>...), the operators <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;+&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">+</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\cdot&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span></span></span></span></span>, and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\^&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">^</span></span></span></span></span> and the relations <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;=&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">=</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;&lt;&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>If a the meaningful expression 'by arithmetic' follows a claim, Lurch will try to use the CAS&nbsp;<a href="http://algebrite.org">Algebrite </a>to determine if the given claim is valid.&nbsp; The claim must be an equation or inequality which only involves natural number constants (e.g. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;3, &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">3,</span></span></span></span></span>...), the operators <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;+&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">+</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\cdot&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span></span></span></span></span>, and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\^&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">^</span></span></span></span></span> and the relations <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;=&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">=</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;&lt;&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span></span></span></span></span>. For example, it can check something like this:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2^{10}+1=10^3+5^2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">10</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">10</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">3</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">5</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p>and inequalities like this</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2^{10}&lt;3^7&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">10</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__cmr">3</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">7</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p>but will be inapplicable to something like this because it uses the negation operator (which isn't one of the allowed operators)</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2^{10}-1=1023&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">10</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">1023</span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">or something like this, because it contains a variable</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0 \\leq x^2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p></div>
        </div></div><div class="lurch-atom-body"><table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><b>Imported dependency document</b></td></tr><tr><td>Description:</td><td><tt>none</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Filename:</td><td><tt>learn/proofs/rules/Arithmetic-naturals-Rules.lurch</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Source:</td><td>the web</td></tr><tr><td>Auto-refresh:</td><td>yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div>
            <div id="document"><h1>Induction Theorems</h1>
<p>Induction is such a useful method of proof that it is convenient to have some additional flavors of the induction rule that are useful in many situations.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Declare in, +, leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Declare </span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span></span></span></span></span> to be a constants.</p>
<hr>
<div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Induction</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="Premise:">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<p><em><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(0)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.64444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let k be such that k in NN and @P(k)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__text"> be such that </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.69444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(k+1)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.08333em; height: 0.77777em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;forall n in NN.@P(n)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Strong induction</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="Premise:">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<p><em><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(0)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.64444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let k be such that k in NN and (forall j in NN.j leq k implies @P(j))&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__text"> be such that </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">⇒</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.85396em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(k+1)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.08333em; height: 0.77777em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;forall n in NN.@P(n)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Induction from <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;a&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span></span></span></span></span></strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="Premise:">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<p><em><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(a)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let k be such that k in NN and a leq k and @P(k)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__text"> be such that </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.69444em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;@P(k+1)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.08333em; height: 0.77777em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;forall n in NN.a leq n implies @P(n)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">⇒</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
</div>
</div></div>
        </div></div><div class="lurch-atom-body"><table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><b>Imported dependency document</b></td></tr><tr><td>Description:</td><td><tt>none</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Filename:</td><td><tt>learn/proofs/rules/Induction-Rules.lurch</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Source:</td><td>the web</td></tr><tr><td>Auto-refresh:</td><td>yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div>
            <div id="document"><h1>Set Theory</h1>
<p>We now define a formal system for elementary naive set theory.</p>
<h3>Constants</h3>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Declare nonempty, subset, cap, cup, complement, setminus , powerset, cross, set, Union, Intersect, setbuilder&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Declare nonempty, </span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">∩</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">∪</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.81em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__script" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__text">, set, </span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋃</span></span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋂</span></span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__text">setbuilder</span></span></span></span></span> to be constants.</p>
<h3>Definitions</h3>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Empty set&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x notin {}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∉</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Nonempty</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A is nonempty&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__text"> is nonempty</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A neq { }&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;exists x.x in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">∃</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Set</strong> builder&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in { z : @P(z) } equiv @P(x)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.25em; height: 1em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">:</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><strong>Finite set notation:</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in {a} equiv x=a&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in {a,b} equiv x=a or x=b&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in set(a,b,c) equiv x=a or x=b or x=c&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in {a,b,c,d} equiv \nx=a or x=b or x=c or x=d&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Useful trivialities</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in {a}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in {a,b}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in {a,b}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in {a,b,c} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in {a,b,c} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;c in {a,b,c} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in {a,b,c,d} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in {a,b,c,d} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;c in {a,b,c,d} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;d in {a,b,c,d} &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">{</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">d</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">}</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<div>
<div>
<p><strong>Set Relations</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Subset-</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If A subset B, x in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span> then<em> </em><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Subset+</strong>:</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let x in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Conclude </em><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A subset B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Set equality:</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let a in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let b in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A=B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><strong>Sets from other sets</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Powerset</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;A in powerset(B) equiv A subset B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__script" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.68333em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Intersection</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A intersect B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∩</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span> , <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Union</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in A union B equiv x in A or x in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∪</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Relative Complement</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A setminus B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">∖</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span> , <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x notin B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∉</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Complement</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in B complement equiv x notin B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.81em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.39em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∉</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div><hr>
<p><strong>Cartesian product</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Binary <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\times&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">×</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If z in A cross B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span> then&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;z=[a,b] and a in A and b in B for some a,b&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__text"> for some </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Binary <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\times&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">×</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;pair(a,b) in A cross B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in A,&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in B&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Ternary&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\times&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">×</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If z in A cross B cross C&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;z=[a,b,c] and a in A and b in B and c in C for some a,b,c&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span><span class="ML__text"> for some </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Ternary <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\times&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">×</span></span></span></span></span></strong> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;[a,b,c] in A cross B cross C&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.8888799999999999em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">⟨</span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">⟩</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">×</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;a in A&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;b in B,&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">B</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;c in C&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">c</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">C</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<hr><strong>Indexed Union and Intersection</strong>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Indexed Union: </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x in Union i in I of @A(i)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋃</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.65952em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in @A(j) and j in I for some j&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.85396em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span><span class="ML__text"> for some </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Indexed Union: </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If j in I, x in @A(j) &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.85396em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in Union i in I of @A(i)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋃</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.65952em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Indexed Intersection:&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x in Intersect i in I of @A(i), j in I&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋂</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.65952em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in @A(j)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.85396em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Indexed Intersection</strong></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;premise&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><em>Given</em></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;subproof&quot;" data-shell_title="">
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Let j in I&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Let </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in @A(j)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.85396em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.06em;">j</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<p><em>Conclude</em> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in Intersect i in I of @A(i)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__op-group"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.06em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -1.85em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.08em;">I</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.05em;"><span style="height: 1.61em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__op-symbol ML__large-op">⋂</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cal">A</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.65952em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">i</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div></div>
        </div></div><div class="lurch-atom-body"><table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><b>Imported dependency document</b></td></tr><tr><td>Description:</td><td><tt>none</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Filename:</td><td><tt>learn/proofs/rules/Sets-Rules.lurch</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Source:</td><td>the web</td></tr><tr><td>Auto-refresh:</td><td>yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div>
            <div id="document"><div>
<h1>Real Numbers</h1>
</div>
<p>We can now define a formal system for the Real Numbers.</p>
<h3>Constants</h3>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Declare -, *, &lt;&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Declare </span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span></span></span></span></span> to be a constants.</p>
<h3>Axioms</h3>
<p>We include here all of the rules of inference for the real numbers except for the completeness axiom, which is beyond the scope of this course.</p>
<h4><strong>Axioms of Addition</strong></h4>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Additive identity&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x+0=x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0+x=x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Additive inverse&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x+(-x)=0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.08333em; height: 0.66666em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;-x+x=0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Commutativity of addition&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x+y=y+x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Associativity of addition&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(x+y)+z = x+(y+z)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.7777700000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.7777700000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<h4>Axioms of Multiplication</h4>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Multiplicative identity</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;1 neq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;1*x=x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x*1=x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Multiplicative inverse&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x neq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp; then&nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x*x^-=1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.83em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(x^-)*x=1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.821331em;"><span class="ML__open ML__delim-size1">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.83em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__close ML__delim-size1">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Commutativity of multiplication &nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x*y=y*x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Associativity of multiplication</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(x*y)*z =x*(y*z)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.63889em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.63889em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h4>Axioms of Order</h4>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less-than is irreflexive</strong>&nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;not (x &lt; x)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">not </span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.0391em; height: 0.5782em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less-than is transitive&nbsp;</strong> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x&lt;y, y&lt;z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x&lt;z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Trichotomy</strong>&nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x=y or (x&lt;y or y&lt;x)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.7335400000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<h4>Axioms Relating +, ⋅, and &lt;</h4>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Distributivity </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x*(y+z)=x*y+x*z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.7777700000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Translation&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x&lt;y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x+z&lt;y+z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Product of positives</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If 0&lt;x, 0&lt;y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0&lt;x*y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div>The following axiom is not used in our course but we list it here for completeness (pun).</div>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<div><strong>Completion:</strong> Every bounded above set of real numbers has a least upper bound.</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2>Definitions for Real Numbers</h2>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Declare /, positive, negative, nonnegative, nonzero, abs&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Declare </span><span class="ML__cmr">/</span><span class="ML__text">, positive, negative, nonnegative, nonzero, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__text">abs</span></span></span></span></span> to be constants.&nbsp; Note that the definition of subtraction is built-in so that <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;x-y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;x+(-y)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">(−</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">)</span></span></span></span></span> are synonyms.&nbsp; This is not true for quotients.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less than or equal to</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x leq y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x&lt;y or x=y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less than or equal to</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x&lt;y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x leq y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less than or equal to&nbsp;</strong> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x=y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x leq y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Quotient&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If y neq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x/y = x * y^-&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.94em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.63em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.44em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.83em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Positive&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is positive &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is positive</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0&lt;x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Negative</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is negative&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is negative</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x&lt;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Nonnegative&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is nonnegative &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is nonnegative</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0 leq x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Nonzero&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is nonzero &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is nonzero</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x neq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Less than or equal to&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x leq y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x&lt;y or x=y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Absolute value</strong> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If 0 leq x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;abs(x)=x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">∣</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">∣</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span>.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Absolute value</strong> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x&lt;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;abs(x)=-x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: 0em; height: 0.43056em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">∣</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">∣</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<h3>Theorems</h3>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Distributive law on the right&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;(x+y)*z=x*z+y*z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.19444em; height: 0.7777700000000001em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
</div></div>
        </div></div><div class="lurch-atom-body"><table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><b>Imported dependency document</b></td></tr><tr><td>Description:</td><td><tt>none</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Filename:</td><td><tt>learn/proofs/rules/Reals-Rules.lurch</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Source:</td><td>the web</td></tr><tr><td>Auto-refresh:</td><td>yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;dependency&quot;" data-metadata_description="&quot;none&quot;" data-metadata_filename="&quot;learn/proofs/rules/Arithmetic-rationals-Rules.lurch&quot;" data-metadata_source="&quot;the web&quot;" data-metadata_auto-refresh="true" style="border: 1px solid gray; padding: 0px 1em;"><div class="lurch-atom-metadata" style="display: none;"><div data-key="content">
            <div id="loadlink">
                <p><a>Open this file in the Lurch web app</a></p>
                
            </div>
        
            <div id="metadata" style="display: none;"><div data-category="settings" data-key="shell style" data-value-type="json">"boxed"</div><div data-category="main" data-key="header" data-value-type="html"></div></div>
            <div id="document"><h1>Arithmetic in <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{Q}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span></h1>
<p>The Arithmetic Rule for the rationals is a special built-in validation tool that Lurch provides for evaluating arithmetic identities and inequalities involving rational numbers.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Arithmetic in the Rationals Rule. </strong>We allow <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Arithmetic(QQ)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Arithmetic</span><span class="ML__left-right" style="margin-top: -0.16667em; height: 0.85556em;"><span class="ML__small-delim ML__open">(</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span><span class="ML__small-delim ML__close">)</span></span></span></span></span></span> to justify equations or inequality which only involves natural number constants (e.g. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;-2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">−2</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;3/5, &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">3/5,</span></span></span></span></span>...), the operators <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;+&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">+</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\cdot&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;-&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;/&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">/</span></span></span></span></span>and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\^&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">^</span></span></span></span></span> and the relations <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;=&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">=</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;&lt;&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<p>If a the meaningful expression 'by arithmetic' follows a claim, Lurch will try to use the CAS&nbsp;<a href="http://algebrite.org">Algebrite </a>to determine if the given claim is valid.&nbsp; The claim must be an equation or inequality which only involves natural number constants (e.g. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;3, &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">3,</span></span></span></span></span>...), the operators <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;+&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">+</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\cdot&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span></span></span></span></span>,&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\^&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">^</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;-&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;/&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">/</span></span></span></span></span>, and the relations <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;=&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">=</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span></span></span></span></span>, and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;&lt;&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span></span></span></span></span>. For example, it can check something like this:</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\frac{12}{14}=\\frac{7-1}{7}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">14</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">12</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">7</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.73em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">7</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p>and inequalities like this</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\frac{6}{13}&lt;\\frac{4}{7}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">13</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">6</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">7</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">4</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p>but will be inapplicable to something like this because it has a non-integer exponent</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;2^\\frac{1}{2}&lt;2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.16em;"><span style="top: -3.48em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 1.05em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.97em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.46em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 71.43%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 71.43%;"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p>or something like this because it divides by zero</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\frac{0}{2^{10}-1024}=0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.83em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.75em;"><span style="top: -3.28em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">10</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__cmr">1024</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">It is also inapplicable for something like this, because it contains a variable</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;0\\leq x^2&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">≤</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> by arithmetic</p>
<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
        </div></div><div class="lurch-atom-body"><table><colgroup><col><col></colgroup><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><b>Imported dependency document</b></td></tr><tr><td>Description:</td><td><tt>none</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Filename:</td><td><tt>learn/proofs/rules/Arithmetic-rationals-Rules.lurch</tt></td></tr><tr><td>Source:</td><td>the web</td></tr><tr><td>Auto-refresh:</td><td>yes</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div></div>
            <div id="document"><div>
<h1>Number Systems</h1>
</div>
<p>We can define the natural, integers and rational numbers as subsets of the real numbers.</p>
<h3>Constants</h3>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;Declare \&quot;natural number\&quot;,integer, rational&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">Declare natural number, integer, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__text">rational</span></span></span></span></span> to be constants.&nbsp; Note that <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{N}, \\mathbb{Z}, \\mathbb{Q}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span> are declared to be constants by default.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 17.16px;"><strong>Terminology</strong></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Natural.&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is a \&quot;natural number\&quot; equiv  x in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is a natural number</span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Integer.</strong> &nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is an integer equiv x in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is an integer</span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Rational.&nbsp;</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x is rational equiv x in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__text"> is rational</span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<h3>Relationships between the sets</h3>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Natural Numbers</strong></p>
<p>1. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0 in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p>2. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;-1 notin NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">−1</span><span class="ML__cmr">∉</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p>3. <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If n in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n+1 in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span><br>4. If <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathcal{P}(0)\\text{ and }\\forall k\\in\\mathbb{N}.\\mathcal{P}(k)\\Rightarrow\\mathcal{P}(k+1)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__cmr">(0)</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__cmr">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">)</span><span class="ML__cmr">⇒</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__cmr">(</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__cmr">1)</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\forall n \\in \\mathbb{N}.\\mathcal{P}(n)&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">∀</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__cal" style="margin-right: 0.09em;">P</span><span class="ML__cmr">(</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">)</span></span></span></span></span>.&nbsp; (see the rules for induction)</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Integers&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n in ZZ equiv n in NN or -n in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__cmr">≡&nbsp;</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text"> or </span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Rational Numbers&nbsp;</strong> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;if x = a/b, a in ZZ, b in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">if </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.94em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.7em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.44em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Rational Numbers&nbsp;</strong> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If r in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.03em;">r</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;r=a/b and a in ZZ and b in ZZ for some a,b&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.03em;">r</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.94em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.7em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">b</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.44em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">a</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__text"> and </span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__text"> for some </span><span class="ML__mathit">a</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">b</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Positives &nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A^+ &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.83em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot; equiv&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&nbsp;≡&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x in A, 0&lt;x&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__mathit">A</span><span class="ML__cmr">,</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&lt;</span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<h3>Extended Definitions</h3>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Integer Exponents&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If z neq 0, n in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;z^0=1&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span></span>,&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;z^(n+1)=z*z^n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.51em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">+1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.72em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.31em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;z^(-n)=1/z^n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.83em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.47em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 1.15em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.6em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.6em;"><span style="top: -3.28em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.31em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.65em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__cmr">1</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<h3>Theorems</h3>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Integers. </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If -n in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot; n in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Inclusions.</strong> <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;NN subset ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>,&nbsp; <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;ZZ subset QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;NN subset QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">⊆</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Closure of <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{N}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>. </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If n in NN, m in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n+m in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n*m in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>, and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n^2 in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Closure of <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{Z}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>. </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If n in ZZ, m in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n+m in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n*m in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n-m in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n^2 in ZZ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Z</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom unindented" data-metadata_type="&quot;rule&quot;" data-shell_title="Rule:">
<p><strong>Closure of <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{Q}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>. </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If n in QQ, m in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n+m in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n*m in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">⋅</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n-m in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">−</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n/m in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mfrac"><span class="ML__vlist-t ML__vlist-t2"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.94em;"><span class="ML__center" style="top: -2.31em;"><span style="height: 0.44em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">m</span></span></span><span class="ML__center" style="top: -3.5em;"><span style="height: 0.44em; display: inline-block;"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__vlist-s">​</span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span> (if <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;m\\neq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__rlap"><span class="ML__inner"><span class="ML__cmr"></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>) and <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n^2 in QQ&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__msubsup"><span class="ML__vlist-t"><span class="ML__vlist-r"><span class="ML__vlist" style="height: 0.87em;"><span style="top: -3.41em; margin-right: 0.05em;"><span style="height: 0.46em; display: inline-block; font-size: 70%;"><span class="ML__cmr">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class="ML__cmr">∈</span><span class="ML__bb">Q</span></span></span></span></span>.&