            <div id="document"><p><span style="color: rgb(126, 140, 141);">Name:</span></p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Assignment 19</h1>
<h4 style="text-align: center;">Due: Thursday, April 21</h4>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Here it is, future mathematicians!&nbsp; More proofs!&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>On this assignment we will try to prove that Peano axiom I holds for the set or real numbers&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\mathbb{N}&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> by proving a sequence of results that lead to the conclusion.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - easy<br><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - moderate<br><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> - more challenging</span></p>
<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 1.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Hint: proof by cases</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem (<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span></span></span></span></span> is transitive).&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x leq y, y leq z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x leq z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 2.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Hint: Proof by cases.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem (translation for <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\leq&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span></span></span></span></span>) . </strong>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If x leq y&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;x+z leq y+z&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">x</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">y</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.05em;">z</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 3.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Hint: Induction!</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Lemma (zero is smallest).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If n in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;0 leq n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 4.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Hint: No induction needed.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Corollary (seriously, it's smallest).&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If m in NN, m leq 0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;m=0&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 5.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span> Hint: Induction from <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;m&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">m</span></span></span></span></span>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem (natural differences).&nbsp; </strong><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If m in NN, n in NN, m leq n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;n-m in NN&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">&minus;</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:&nbsp;</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 6.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem (Peano Axiom <span style="font-family: 'andale mono', monospace;">I <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\Leftarrow&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&lArr;</span></span></span></span></span></span>).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If 0 leq k, m+k=n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__cmr">0</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text"> and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;m leq n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p><span style="background-color: rgb(45, 194, 107); color: rgb(236, 240, 241);">&nbsp; Problem 7.<strong> </strong></span>&nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\star&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">⋆</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;theorem&quot;" data-shell_title="Theorem:">
<p><strong>Theorem (Peano Axiom <span style="font-family: 'andale mono', monospace;">I <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\Rightarrow&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&rArr;</span></span></span></span></span></span>).</strong> &nbsp;<span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;If m in NN, n in NN, m leq n &quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__text">If </span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__text">, </span><span style="color: #000000;"><span class="ML__text">and </span></span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">&le;</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span> then <span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expression&quot;" data-metadata_lurch-notation="&quot;exists k in NN.m+k=n&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__cmr">&exist;</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">&isin;</span><span class="ML__bb">N</span><span class="ML__cmr">.</span><span class="ML__mathit">m</span><span class="ML__cmr">+</span><span class="ML__mathit" style="margin-right: 0.04em;">k</span><span class="ML__cmr">=</span><span class="ML__mathit">n</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="lurch-atom" data-metadata_type="&quot;proof&quot;" data-shell_title="Proof:">
<p><strong>Proof:</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class="lurch-atom" contenteditable="false" data-metadata_type="&quot;expositorymath&quot;" data-metadata_latex="&quot;\\square&quot;"><span class="lurch-atom-body"><span class="ML__latex"><span class="ML__base"><span class="ML__ams">□</span></span></span></span></span></p>
</div>
<hr>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
        